definitions.definition: Open to debate ; not fully proved or confirmed .
examples: Those data are debatable : no one has been able to replicate them.
It's debatable whether he is the best candidate for the position.

definitions.definition: Able to be debated ; up for discussion .
examples: The lack of bonuses this year is not debatable .

main_definition: Open to debate ; not fully proved or confirmed .
secondary_definitions: Able to be debated ; up for discussion .
